<item>
            <title>[VCST-3156] [E2E] Detect, Track, and Resolve Broken Links</title>
                <link>https://virtocommerce.atlassian.net/browse/VCST-3156</link>
                <project id="10092" key="VCST">VirtoStart</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As a store administrator using Virto Commerce,&lt;br/&gt;
I want a centralized module to detect, view, and resolve broken URLs (dead permalinks) reported by the storefront when a slugInfo GraphQL query returns empty results and frontend display 404 error,&lt;br/&gt;
so that I can improve the customer experience by fixing broken navigation, maintaining SEO integrity, and reducing bounce rates from 404 errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;BusinessValue%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Business Value:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Improve customer experience:&lt;/b&gt; Automatically detects broken links and lets admins resolve them via redirects, so shoppers don&#8217;t hit dead ends.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;SEO optimization:&lt;/b&gt; Minimizes 404s that negatively impact SEO rankings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Operational efficiency:&lt;/b&gt; Gives non-technical users easy control over broken link resolution via a clean back office interface.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Data-driven maintenance:&lt;/b&gt; Provides usage insights (detection count, last modified) to prioritize fixes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
