                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;1.DetectionandDashboardAccess%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. Detection and Dashboard Access:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the storefront opens a &lt;tt&gt;seoSlug&lt;/tt&gt; GraphQL query and nothing is found, the system logs the event as a &lt;em&gt;Broken Page&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Admins can access a &lt;b&gt;&#8220;Broken Page&#8221; widget&lt;/b&gt; in the back office dashboard for each store.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Clicking the widget opens a &lt;b&gt;Broken Page Grid View&lt;/b&gt; scoped to the selected store.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;2.GridViewFiltersandData%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;2. Grid View Filters and Data:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The grid supports filtering by status: &lt;tt&gt;Active&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;Resolved&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;Accepted&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;All&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Each row displays:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Permalink&lt;/tt&gt; (broken URL)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Language&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Count&lt;/tt&gt; of detections&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Created&lt;/tt&gt; timestamp&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Last Modified&lt;/tt&gt; timestamp&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Status &lt;tt&gt;Active&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;Resolved&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;Accepted&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;StoreId&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;3.ResolvingBrokenPageswithRedirects%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;3. Resolving Broken Pages with Redirects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Clicking a row allows the admin to assign a &lt;b&gt;new redirect permalink&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Upon saving, the status of the broken page changes to &lt;b&gt;Resolved&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The UI provides a brief &lt;b&gt;description of what entity&lt;/b&gt; the redirect points to (e.g., &#8220;Redirected to Product: Red Shoes&#8221;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;4.RedirectFallbackBehaviour%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;4. Redirect Fallback Behaviour:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the frontend encounters a previously resolved broken link again, the &lt;b&gt;new redirect permalink&lt;/b&gt; is used automatically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;5.AcceptWithoutAction%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;5. Accept Without Action:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Admins may choose to mark a broken page as &lt;b&gt;Accepted&lt;/b&gt;, indicating it&#8217;s acknowledged but not actionable (e.g., intentionally removed pages).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Accepted entries are removed from the &lt;tt&gt;Active&lt;/tt&gt; list but retained for audit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;6.UpdatingRedirects%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;6. Updating Redirects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Admins can re-open a resolved entry and &lt;b&gt;change the redirect permalink&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The system updates the status and &lt;tt&gt;modified&lt;/tt&gt; timestamp accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;6.BackupandRestorefunctionality&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;6. Backup and Restore functionality&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;</customfieldvalue>

